captions.text: - Oh, I deleted it.
(laughs) I feel like my dad!
(goofy synth music)
- I've never used Snapchat before.

- No, I haven't, I've
heard about it though.
- I'm a little suspicious.
- Young people love technology
that older people don't know how to use.

- I know that the icon is
a ghost that does, like...

- I was sure that it was
just for nude pictures.
- I could send pictures of my junk

and then it's just gonna be
gone in 30 seconds or something.
- [Interviewer] Exactly.

There's a real appeal to
that, I'll have to tell ya.
- Then it became clear that teens
were just sending funny images.

- I'm ready to snap.
(brass bell rings)
- I have to take an ugly selfie?

I don't wanna, this is
why I don't like Snapchat.

- Those are the rules, it

So I'm gonna reinvent the selfie.

- This gives me an

It's really bad, this is
just me bashing myself.
- Ooh, that's ugly.
- Oh, I think I hit the wrong thing.
- Dude, I am so wasted.
- You should always do a dumb face,

Date me! (creepy laugh)
- I am so cutting edge.
- Now where are my filters?
Ooh, I can write that it's 3:20?
I'm gonna go with Hypercolorful.

My stupid fat fingers, I
feel like I'm doing great.

- Is your mom on here,
can I send it to your mom?
Oh, damn it.

- What's this stopwatch
in the bottom left?
- Is that my timer?
- Who would ever do one second?

That would be just rude, well,
I guess if it's your dick.

- It's still sad that the
picture's gone in 10 seconds.

- I'm gonna take a video.
- What'll my video be about?

(camera shutter clicks)
- Ooh.
Oh, what a minute, what'd I do?
- Whoa! Space.
Everyone's gonna see this and be like,
"When did Alison become an astronaut?"

- And now I'm gonna start
talking, and send it to my buddy?
- I'm gonna do my best impression,
Cal from the film Titanic.

I put the jewel in the coat,
and I put the coat on her!
(laughs) Oh, was that dumb?
- This is what my face would look like
if my nostrils were my eyes.
- This is like a J.J. Abrams selfie.
This combines drawing and selfies,

which are two things
I'm terrible at doing.
So this is like, if I was like,
"Hey do you guys wanna come watch me

"dance and do my own
taxes at the same time?"

- And the message I would
like to give people is,

don't waste your time
sweating the small stuff.

Life is too short.
- Oh, you can watch it

for an unlimited amount
of time for 24 hours.

- I'm about to view my best

Okay, now she's at the MTV Movie Awards.
Cool, she didn't invite me to that.
I have a lot to say to Gaby.

- We had a version of this
when I was in middle school
and it was just passing notes.

- If I was in high school,

- I can get into it, but I also like

You know when people create

takes it away on the
sand, like on beaches?
(bleep) that.

- You know, I mean they

so there's worse things
to do than Snapchat.
- It's more fun than I thought.

- I thought it was stupid,
but now I'm enjoying it.

- I just hope people
don't get carried away
using it for sex pictures all the time.
In my day, we had the Polaroid for that.

But then you could just
throw it away. (laughs)

- What's the terminology,
"I got Snapchatted"?
"I'm snapping"? I'm snapping.
Snappin' 'dis chat, yo.

comments.text:
I don't think snapchat is as useless as people make it out to be. I use it 
to tell my international friends about life in the USA. When I have WiFi, 
it's free texting, both nationally and internationally. It expresses more 
than text; if you send someone a text message of something you're joking 
about, but you don't make it CLEAR that you're joking, it could be 
offensive. Sending a video pretty much guarantees clarity. I ignore other 
people's stories for the most part, but when I travel, I share my 
adventures with my friends on my story--and it's relatively instant. I 
don't have to upload it on Facebook, it just pops up in my story or in my 
friend's inbox. And it's not going to get lost in the jumble that is 
someone's Facebook newsfeed, which is a mess. It has uses, it depends on 
the person.﻿
